                      <items count="6">
                        <item name="Description" type_name="gh_string" type_code="10">Rounds the O-grid inner core from a square (0) toward a circle (1). Higher values even out the radial gap to the outer boundary, cutting the corner non-orthogonality of the square core. 0 keeps the classic square core. 0.65 is the checkMesh-sweep optimum (lowest max non-orthogonality across mesh resolutions; skewness stays well within limits). Default: 0.65.</item>
